https://learn.chef.io/tutorials/learn-the-basics/rhel/aws/configure-a-resource/

Use local Chef to update a Message of the Day file in the /tmp dir

1. create a chef working directory to put your chef recipes files on the ec2 server
mkdir ~/chef-repo
cd ~/chef-repo

2. Create a recipe file in the working directory on your ec2

touch hello.rb
vi/emacs/nano hello.rb
copy and paste the below code

file '/tmp/motd' do
  content 'hello world'
end


3. Run the chef client command on the ec2 server
chef-client --local-mode hello.rb

4. Run the more command on your EC2 to view your newly created file
more /tmp/motd


